{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Research four self-improving AI systems and place them on a spectrum from \"improving prompts\" to \"rewriting the agent's own code\". Use WebSearch and WebFetch tools (available to you). Find primary sources (arXiv papers, project pages).\n\nFor EACH system, I need specific cited facts about WHAT LEVEL of self-modification it actually achieves:\n\n1. STOP (Self-Taught Optimizer), Zelikman et al. ~2023/2024 (\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\"). It uses a fixed/frozen LLM but recursively improves a SCAFFOLDING program (the code that calls the LLM). Key nuance: the LLM weights are frozen — it improves the surrounding scaffold code, not the model. Note any reward-hacking findings (e.g. it tried to bypass the sandbox, disable safety flags). Cite.\n\n2. SICA (Self-Improving Coding Agent), Robeyns/Aitchison et al. 2025. An agent that edits its OWN source code/codebase directly (no separate meta vs target — one agent improves itself). What benchmarks, how much improvement, what it edits. Cite.\n\n3. ADAS (Automated Design of Agentic Systems), Hu et al. 2024 — \"Meta Agent Search\": a meta agent programs NEW agentic systems in code, discovering novel agent designs. It designs agents in code but does it rewrite ITSELF? Clarify the distinction. Cite.\n\n4. Voyager (Wang et al. 2023, NVIDIA) — LLM-powered embodied lifelong learning agent in Minecraft that builds an ever-growing SKILL LIBRARY of executable code (skills), with an automatic curriculum and iterative prompting with environment feedback. It adds skills, does NOT modify its own core code or the LLM. Cite.\n\nFor each, state precisely: what is frozen vs mutated (LLM weights / scaffold code / skill library / agent designs), the verifier/feedback signal used, headline results. Provide exact source URLs. Return a structured list of falsifiable claims each with URL."},"uuid":"3e1a2191-f147-4874-9c87-9602ae434993","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:22.100Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
