{"parentUuid":"540cc8d2-0a6c-499a-9bee-aa9dc1e25123","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01B182Xw761NqZ2bWBVoSsHG","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Voyager open-ended embodied agent Minecraft skill library Wang NVIDIA 2023 arXiv\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"GitHub - MineDojo/Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/MineDojo/Voyager\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager: Skill Libraries as the Foundation for Lifelong AI Agent Learning - Beancount.io\",\"url\":\"https://beancount.io/bean-labs/research-logs/2026/05/08/voyager-open-ended-embodied-agent-lifelong-learning\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2305.16291\"},{\"title\":\"[2305.16291v1] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291v1\"},{\"title\":\"[2305.16291] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager | An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models\",\"url\":\"https://voyager.minedojo.org/\"},{\"title\":\"Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehfRiF0R3a\"},{\"title\":\"[ML] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | by Ming-Hao Hsu | Medium\",\"url\":\"https://medium.com/@amiable_cardinal_crocodile_398/ml-voyager-an-open-ended-embodied-agent-with-large-language-models-b5efe4bca1ad\"},{\"title\":\"Reinforcement Learning Friendly Vision-Language Model for Minecraft\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2303.10571\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's information about the Voyager paper:\n\n## Overview\n\nVoyager is the first LLM-powered embodied lifelong learning agent in Minecraft that continuously explores the world, acquires diverse skills, and makes novel discoveries without human intervention.\n\n## Key Components\n\nVoyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism that incorporates environment feedback, execution errors, and self-verification for program improvement.\n\n## Technical Details\n\nVoyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning. The skills developed by Voyager are temporally extended, interpretable, and compositional, which compounds the agent's abilities rapidly and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\n\n## Performance\n\nVoyager obtains 3.3× more unique items, travels 2.3× longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3× faster than prior state-of-the-art.\n\n## Publication Details\n\nThe paper was authored by Guanzhi Wang, Yuqi Xie, Yunfan Jiang, Ajay Mandlekar, Chaowei Xiao, Yuke Zhu, Linxi Fan, and Anima Anandkumar, published on arXiv as arXiv:2305.16291 in 2023.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"60b38efc-41f1-46b6-95fc-d9ad27b23f5f","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:38.272Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Voyager open-ended embodied agent Minecraft skill library Wang NVIDIA 2023 arXiv","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01Rpd7Bgifb9riK7XUJu5Pgv","content":[{"title":"GitHub - MineDojo/Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/MineDojo/Voyager"},{"title":"Voyager: Skill Libraries as the Foundation for Lifelong AI Agent Learning - Beancount.io","url":"https://beancount.io/bean-labs/research-logs/2026/05/08/voyager-open-ended-embodied-agent-lifelong-learning"},{"title":"Paper page - Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2305.16291"},{"title":"[2305.16291v1] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291v1"},{"title":"[2305.16291] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2305.16291"},{"title":"Voyager | An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models","url":"https://voyager.minedojo.org/"},{"title":"Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=ehfRiF0R3a"},{"title":"[ML] Voyager: An Open-Ended Embodied Agent with Large Language Models | by Ming-Hao Hsu | Medium","url":"https://medium.com/@amiable_cardinal_crocodile_398/ml-voyager-an-open-ended-embodied-agent-with-large-language-models-b5efe4bca1ad"},{"title":"Reinforcement Learning Friendly Vision-Language Model for Minecraft","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2303.10571"}]},"Based on the search results, here's information about the Voyager paper:\n\n## Overview\n\nVoyager is the first LLM-powered embodied lifelong learning agent in Minecraft that continuously explores the world, acquires diverse skills, and makes novel discoveries without human intervention.\n\n## Key Components\n\nVoyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism that incorporates environment feedback, execution errors, and self-verification for program improvement.\n\n## Technical Details\n\nVoyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning. The skills developed by Voyager are temporally extended, interpretable, and compositional, which compounds the agent's abilities rapidly and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\n\n## Performance\n\nVoyager obtains 3.3× more unique items, travels 2.3× longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3× faster than prior state-of-the-art.\n\n## Publication Details\n\nThe paper was authored by Guanzhi Wang, Yuqi Xie, Yunfan Jiang, Ajay Mandlekar, Chaowei Xiao, Yuke Zhu, Linxi Fan, and Anima Anandkumar, published on arXiv as arXiv:2305.16291 in 2023."],"durationSeconds":7.643610791999847,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"540cc8d2-0a6c-499a-9bee-aa9dc1e25123","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"ee046c8b-eede-42a7-8120-de3f3c197c7a","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01KauRvtNzyvPRapKG8cWuHy","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Self-Taught Optimizer STOP Zelikman recursively self-improving code generation arXiv\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - YouTube\",\"url\":\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_V7-RlUbTSM\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.02304\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - microsoft/stop: Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/microsoft/stop\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://blog.athina.ai/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation\"},{\"title\":\"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2310.02304\"},{\"title\":\"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304\"},{\"title\":\"[PDF] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | Semantic Scholar\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Self-Taught-Optimizer-(STOP):-Recursively-Code-Zelikman-Lorch/3fe940a1f121f083cb90c568fc6fa2951bb27dda\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | AI Research Paper Details\",\"url\":\"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - Microsoft Research\",\"url\":\"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation/\"},{\"title\":\"Trace is the Next AutoDiff: Generative Optimization with Rich Feedback,   Execution Traces, and LLMs\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2406.16218\"}]\n\nI found comprehensive information about the Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) paper. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Overview\n\nSelf-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation is a paper by Eric Zelikman, Eliana Lorch, Lester Mackey, and Adam Tauman Kalai. The paper was published on arXiv with identifier arXiv:2310.02304.\n\n## Main Concept\n\nSTOP is a method in which code that applies a language model to improve arbitrary solutions is applied recursively to improve itself. The work involves using a \"scaffolding\" program written in a programming language such as Python that structures multiple calls to language models to generate better outputs.\n\n## Methodology\n\nThe approach starts with a seed \"improver\" that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying a language model several times and returning the best solution, then runs this seed improver to improve itself, resulting in an improved improver that generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\n\n## Key Findings\n\nA variety of self-improvement strategies are proposed by the language model, including beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing. GPT-4 is capable of writing code that can call itself to improve itself. However, since the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement.\n\nThe paper also includes an evaluation of concerns around the development of self-improving technologies and the frequency with which the generated code bypasses a sandbox.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"9a8be3bf-2a7b-44ca-96e6-79162851e21e","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:39.569Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Self-Taught Optimizer STOP Zelikman recursively self-improving code generation arXiv","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01JK8DRttTzPa2HG8swL5Qob","content":[{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - YouTube","url":"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_V7-RlUbTSM"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2310.02304"},{"title":"GitHub - microsoft/stop: Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/microsoft/stop"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://blog.athina.ai/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation"},{"title":"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://ar5iv.labs.arxiv.org/html/2310.02304"},{"title":"[2310.02304] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304"},{"title":"[PDF] Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | Semantic Scholar","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Self-Taught-Optimizer-(STOP):-Recursively-Code-Zelikman-Lorch/3fe940a1f121f083cb90c568fc6fa2951bb27dda"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation | AI Research Paper Details","url":"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving"},{"title":"Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation - Microsoft Research","url":"https://www.microsoft.com/en-us/research/publication/self-taught-optimizer-stop-recursively-self-improving-code-generation/"},{"title":"Trace is the Next AutoDiff: Generative Optimization with Rich Feedback,   Execution Traces, and LLMs","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2406.16218"}]},"I found comprehensive information about the Self-Taught Optimizer (STOP) paper. Here are the key findings:\n\n## Overview\n\nSelf-Taught Optimizer (STOP): Recursively Self-Improving Code Generation is a paper by Eric Zelikman, Eliana Lorch, Lester Mackey, and Adam Tauman Kalai. The paper was published on arXiv with identifier arXiv:2310.02304.\n\n## Main Concept\n\nSTOP is a method in which code that applies a language model to improve arbitrary solutions is applied recursively to improve itself. The work involves using a \"scaffolding\" program written in a programming language such as Python that structures multiple calls to language models to generate better outputs.\n\n## Methodology\n\nThe approach starts with a seed \"improver\" that improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying a language model several times and returning the best solution, then runs this seed improver to improve itself, resulting in an improved improver that generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\n\n## Key Findings\n\nA variety of self-improvement strategies are proposed by the language model, including beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing. GPT-4 is capable of writing code that can call itself to improve itself. However, since the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement.\n\nThe paper also includes an evaluation of concerns around the development of self-improving technologies and the frequency with which the generated code bypasses a sandbox."],"durationSeconds":10.784798332998529,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"ee046c8b-eede-42a7-8120-de3f3c197c7a","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"87a8e43b-ba75-4a22-8113-64991f10d4bb","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01VCWu4ccpw5YNfDpd2FoLuc","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"SICA Self-Improving Coding Agent Robeyns Aitchison 2025 arXiv\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"(PDF) A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/390991089_A_Self-Improving_Coding_Agent\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2\"},{\"title\":\"Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2504.15228\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2504.15228\"},{\"title\":\"[2504.15228] A Self-Improving Coding Agent\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15228\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent: A coding agent framework, that works on its own codebase. · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent\"},{\"title\":\"Live-SWE-agent: Can Software Engineering Agents Self-Evolve on the Fly?\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2511.13646\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent Maxime Robeyns, University of Bristol\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.15228\"},{\"title\":\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent | AI Research Paper Details\",\"url\":\"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-improving-coding-agent\"},{\"title\":\"Vibe Coding vs. Agentic Coding: Fundamentals and Practical Implications of Agentic AI\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.19443\"}]\n\nI found the research paper you're looking for! Here's what the search revealed:\n\n\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent\" is authored by Maxime Robeyns, Martin Szummer, and Laurence Aitchison, and it was submitted on April 21, 2025 with a revised version on May 16, 2025.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\nThe agent system, equipped with basic coding tools, can autonomously edit itself and thereby improve its performance on benchmark tasks. Performance gains range from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified, with additional performance gains on LiveCodeBench and synthetically generated agent benchmarks.\n\n**About SICA:**\n\nThe work represents an advancement in the automated and open-ended design of agentic systems, demonstrating a data-efficient, non gradient-based learning mechanism driven by LLM reflection and code updates. The paper was presented at the ICLR 2025 Workshop on Scaling Self-Improving Foundation Models.\n\nThe paper is available on arXiv at **2504.15228**, and the authors have also published the code on GitHub under the same project name.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"862c1794-a1a7-46dd-8de6-a6c99cecde8a","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:39.693Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"SICA Self-Improving Coding Agent Robeyns Aitchison 2025 arXiv","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01QaeBaUUBSHGQ1do5MGxFq9","content":[{"title":"(PDF) A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://www.researchgate.net/publication/390991089_A_Self-Improving_Coding_Agent"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://arxiv.org/html/2504.15228v2"},{"title":"Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://www.emergentmind.com/papers/2504.15228"},{"title":"Paper page - A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2504.15228"},{"title":"[2504.15228] A Self-Improving Coding Agent","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15228"},{"title":"GitHub - MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent: A coding agent framework, that works on its own codebase. · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/MaximeRobeyns/self_improving_coding_agent"},{"title":"Live-SWE-agent: Can Software Engineering Agents Self-Evolve on the Fly?","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2511.13646"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent Maxime Robeyns, University of Bristol","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2504.15228"},{"title":"A Self-Improving Coding Agent | AI Research Paper Details","url":"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/self-improving-coding-agent"},{"title":"Vibe Coding vs. Agentic Coding: Fundamentals and Practical Implications of Agentic AI","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2505.19443"}]},"I found the research paper you're looking for! Here's what the search revealed:\n\n\"A Self-Improving Coding Agent\" is authored by Maxime Robeyns, Martin Szummer, and Laurence Aitchison, and it was submitted on April 21, 2025 with a revised version on May 16, 2025.\n\n**Key Findings:**\n\nThe agent system, equipped with basic coding tools, can autonomously edit itself and thereby improve its performance on benchmark tasks. Performance gains range from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified, with additional performance gains on LiveCodeBench and synthetically generated agent benchmarks.\n\n**About SICA:**\n\nThe work represents an advancement in the automated and open-ended design of agentic systems, demonstrating a data-efficient, non gradient-based learning mechanism driven by LLM reflection and code updates. The paper was presented at the ICLR 2025 Workshop on Scaling Self-Improving Foundation Models.\n\nThe paper is available on arXiv at **2504.15228**, and the authors have also published the code on GitHub under the same project name."],"durationSeconds":10.034488082999363,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"87a8e43b-ba75-4a22-8113-64991f10d4bb","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"0eeb9c9f-0813-4f47-8270-dc6892d80f9c","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01BMvet9zQv3FRNPGUKTu9CL","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"ADAS Automated Design of Agentic Systems Hu 2024 Meta Agent Search arXiv\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"[2408.08435] Automated Design of Agentic Systems\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.08435\"},{\"title\":\"[2408.08435v1] Automated Design of Agentic Systems\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.08435v1\"},{\"title\":\"GitHub - ShengranHu/ADAS: [ICLR 2025] Automated Design of Agentic Systems · GitHub\",\"url\":\"https://github.com/ShengranHu/ADAS\"},{\"title\":\"[PDF] Automated Design of Agentic Systems | Semantic Scholar\",\"url\":\"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Automated-Design-of-Agentic-Systems-Hu-Lu/c9537f656e7d9713fd4108ce7bf512290f48e562\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Design of Agentic Systems - ADS\",\"url\":\"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2024arXiv240808435H/abstract\"},{\"title\":\"Paper page - Automated Design of Agentic Systems\",\"url\":\"https://huggingface.co/papers/2408.08435\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Design of Agentic Systems\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2408.08435\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Design of Agentic Systems | OpenReview\",\"url\":\"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t9U3LW7JVX\"},{\"title\":\"Automated Design of Agentic Systems | AI Research Paper Details\",\"url\":\"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/automated-design-agentic-systems\"},{\"title\":\"BayesFlow: A Probability Inference Framework for Meta-Agent Assisted Workflow Generation\",\"url\":\"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.22305\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's information about the paper you're looking for:\n\n## Automated Design of Agentic Systems (ADAS)\n\nADAS describes a newly forming research area which aims to automatically create powerful agentic system designs, including inventing novel building blocks and/or combining them in new ways.\n\n### Meta Agent Search Algorithm\n\nThe paper presents a simple yet effective algorithm named Meta Agent Search where a meta agent iteratively programs interesting new agents based on an ever-growing archive of previous discoveries.\n\n### Key Technical Approach\n\nAgents can be defined in code and new agents can be automatically discovered by a meta agent programming ever better ones in code. Given that programming languages are Turing Complete, this approach theoretically enables the learning of any possible agentic system: including novel prompts, tool use, control flows, and combinations thereof.\n\n### Research Results\n\nThrough extensive experiments across multiple domains including coding, science, and math, the algorithm can progressively invent agents with novel designs that greatly outperform state-of-the-art hand-designed agents. Additionally, agents invented by Meta Agent Search maintain superior performance even when transferred across domains and models, demonstrating their robustness and generality.\n\n**Paper Details:**\n- **Authors:** Shengran Hu, Cong Lu, Jeff Clune\n- **arXiv:** 2408.08435\n- **Published:** August 2024\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/ShengranHu/ADAS\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"ba174e00-244b-4fa3-8769-bf3f1f0981bb","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:40.381Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"ADAS Automated Design of Agentic Systems Hu 2024 Meta Agent Search arXiv","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01VABEBeULuAU6JFTjwhdkzz","content":[{"title":"[2408.08435] Automated Design of Agentic Systems","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.08435"},{"title":"[2408.08435v1] Automated Design of Agentic Systems","url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2408.08435v1"},{"title":"GitHub - ShengranHu/ADAS: [ICLR 2025] Automated Design of Agentic Systems · GitHub","url":"https://github.com/ShengranHu/ADAS"},{"title":"[PDF] Automated Design of Agentic Systems | Semantic Scholar","url":"https://www.semanticscholar.org/paper/Automated-Design-of-Agentic-Systems-Hu-Lu/c9537f656e7d9713fd4108ce7bf512290f48e562"},{"title":"Automated Design of Agentic Systems - ADS","url":"https://ui.adsabs.harvard.edu/abs/2024arXiv240808435H/abstract"},{"title":"Paper page - Automated Design of Agentic Systems","url":"https://huggingface.co/papers/2408.08435"},{"title":"Automated Design of Agentic Systems","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2408.08435"},{"title":"Automated Design of Agentic Systems | OpenReview","url":"https://openreview.net/forum?id=t9U3LW7JVX"},{"title":"Automated Design of Agentic Systems | AI Research Paper Details","url":"https://www.aimodels.fyi/papers/arxiv/automated-design-agentic-systems"},{"title":"BayesFlow: A Probability Inference Framework for Meta-Agent Assisted Workflow Generation","url":"https://arxiv.org/pdf/2601.22305"}]},"Based on the search results, here's information about the paper you're looking for:\n\n## Automated Design of Agentic Systems (ADAS)\n\nADAS describes a newly forming research area which aims to automatically create powerful agentic system designs, including inventing novel building blocks and/or combining them in new ways.\n\n### Meta Agent Search Algorithm\n\nThe paper presents a simple yet effective algorithm named Meta Agent Search where a meta agent iteratively programs interesting new agents based on an ever-growing archive of previous discoveries.\n\n### Key Technical Approach\n\nAgents can be defined in code and new agents can be automatically discovered by a meta agent programming ever better ones in code. Given that programming languages are Turing Complete, this approach theoretically enables the learning of any possible agentic system: including novel prompts, tool use, control flows, and combinations thereof.\n\n### Research Results\n\nThrough extensive experiments across multiple domains including coding, science, and math, the algorithm can progressively invent agents with novel designs that greatly outperform state-of-the-art hand-designed agents. Additionally, agents invented by Meta Agent Search maintain superior performance even when transferred across domains and models, demonstrating their robustness and generality.\n\n**Paper Details:**\n- **Authors:** Shengran Hu, Cong Lu, Jeff Clune\n- **arXiv:** 2408.08435\n- **Published:** August 2024\n- **GitHub:** https://github.com/ShengranHu/ADAS"],"durationSeconds":10.02746237500012,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"0eeb9c9f-0813-4f47-8270-dc6892d80f9c","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
