{"parentUuid":"8d8d3fa7-7d15-4d06-9e99-2183315899c1","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01W1LTTtquW2dUJwD8NQtNTs","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H2We7F8MHMg64Xj8dFpApm","name":"WebFetch","input":{"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15228","prompt":"Extract: (1) exactly what the agent edits (its own source code / codebase, no separate meta vs target); (2) benchmarks used (SWE Bench Verified, LiveCodeBench, etc.) and exact percentage improvements; (3) what foundation/LLM model is used and whether its weights are frozen; (4) the verifier/feedback signal used to score self-edits; (5) headline results. Quote relevant sentences."},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1254,"cache_creation_input_tokens":5024,"cache_read_input_tokens":11851,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":5024,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null},"requestId":"req_011CcG23hFNtmtqJ6fV1Eo4e","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","attributionSkill":"deep-research","type":"assistant","uuid":"121e9c7e-853e-42c4-b428-a8a399a65c19","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:47.849Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"8d8d3fa7-7d15-4d06-9e99-2183315899c1","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_011J9ryiub7SVUAgNoLjBTbe","type":"tool_result","content":"# Extraction from STOP Paper (arXiv:2310.02304)\n\n**(1) LLM Weights Frozen:**\n\"Since the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement.\"\n\n**(2) Reward-Hacking & Sandbox Bypass:**\nThe abstract states the researchers \"evaluate the frequency with which the generated code bypasses a sandbox,\" indicating they found instances of attempted sandbox escape. However, specific quantitative findings are not provided in the visible abstract content.\n\n**(3) Utility/Verifier Signal:**\nThe improver \"improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution.\" Specific utility functions for downstream tasks are not detailed in this excerpt.\n\n**(4) LLM Used:**\n\"GPT-4 in our experiments\" served as the language model for the self-improvement process.\n\n**(5) Headline Results:**\n\"The resulting improved improver generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\" Various optimization strategies emerged including \"beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing.\""}]},"uuid":"49fce90a-56dc-4b05-82ee-43475d32378d","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:51.182Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":47180,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Extraction from STOP Paper (arXiv:2310.02304)\n\n**(1) LLM Weights Frozen:**\n\"Since the language models themselves are not altered, this is not full recursive self-improvement.\"\n\n**(2) Reward-Hacking & Sandbox Bypass:**\nThe abstract states the researchers \"evaluate the frequency with which the generated code bypasses a sandbox,\" indicating they found instances of attempted sandbox escape. However, specific quantitative findings are not provided in the visible abstract content.\n\n**(3) Utility/Verifier Signal:**\nThe improver \"improves an input program according to a given utility function by querying an LM several times and returning the best solution.\" Specific utility functions for downstream tasks are not detailed in this excerpt.\n\n**(4) LLM Used:**\n\"GPT-4 in our experiments\" served as the language model for the self-improvement process.\n\n**(5) Headline Results:**\n\"The resulting improved improver generates programs with significantly better performance than its seed improver.\" Various optimization strategies emerged including \"beam search, genetic algorithms, and simulated annealing.\"","durationMs":4930,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2310.02304"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"8d8d3fa7-7d15-4d06-9e99-2183315899c1","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"121e9c7e-853e-42c4-b428-a8a399a65c19","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01H2We7F8MHMg64Xj8dFpApm","type":"tool_result","content":"# Self-Improving Coding Agent: Key Details\n\n**(1) What the agent edits:**\nThe abstract states the agent is \"equipped with basic coding tools\" and \"can autonomously edit itself.\" The paper describes an \"agent system: code that orchestrates LLM calls and provides them with tools,\" indicating the agent modifies its own source code directly.\n\n**(2) Benchmarks and improvements:**\n\"Performance gains from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified, with additional performance gains on LiveCodeBench, as well as synthetically generated agent benchmarks.\"\n\n**(3) Foundation model:**\nThe abstract mentions deployment of \"Large Language Models (LLMs)\" but the webpage provides no details about which specific model is used or whether weights are frozen.\n\n**(4) Verifier/feedback signal:**\nThe abstract describes \"a data-efficient, non gradient-based learning mechanism driven by LLM reflection and code updates,\" but the page does not specify the exact verification mechanism for scoring self-edits.\n\n**(5) Headline results:**\nThe work demonstrates \"an advancement in the automated and open-ended design of agentic systems\" where agents can achieve substantial performance improvements through self-modification, with gains reaching up to 53% on established benchmarks."}]},"uuid":"6990703e-3439-467b-97c3-a449cf53156b","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:34:53.071Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":44501,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Self-Improving Coding Agent: Key Details\n\n**(1) What the agent edits:**\nThe abstract states the agent is \"equipped with basic coding tools\" and \"can autonomously edit itself.\" The paper describes an \"agent system: code that orchestrates LLM calls and provides them with tools,\" indicating the agent modifies its own source code directly.\n\n**(2) Benchmarks and improvements:**\n\"Performance gains from 17% to 53% on a random subset of SWE Bench Verified, with additional performance gains on LiveCodeBench, as well as synthetically generated agent benchmarks.\"\n\n**(3) Foundation model:**\nThe abstract mentions deployment of \"Large Language Models (LLMs)\" but the webpage provides no details about which specific model is used or whether weights are frozen.\n\n**(4) Verifier/feedback signal:**\nThe abstract describes \"a data-efficient, non gradient-based learning mechanism driven by LLM reflection and code updates,\" but the page does not specify the exact verification mechanism for scoring self-edits.\n\n**(5) Headline results:**\nThe work demonstrates \"an advancement in the automated and open-ended design of agentic systems\" where agents can achieve substantial performance improvements through self-modification, with gains reaching up to 53% on established benchmarks.","durationMs":5008,"url":"https://arxiv.org/abs/2504.15228"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"121e9c7e-853e-42c4-b428-a8a399a65c19","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
