 key in setup instructions, suggesting OpenAI models, but the specific model (GPT-4, GPT-3.5, etc.) is not stated in this excerpt.\n\n**(2) Archive and Fixed Framework:**\nThe repository confirms the core concept: \"a 'meta' agent iteratively _programs_ interesting new agents in code based on previous discoveries.\" This aligns with your understanding that discovered agents are stored separately while the meta agent framework remains fixed.\n\n**(3) Headline Accuracy Numbers:**\nThe provided content contains no specific accuracy metrics or baseline comparisons. Domain folders are listed (ARC, DROP, MGSM, MMLU, GPQA), but actual performance numbers are absent from this excerpt.\n\n**(4) Evaluation Signal:**\nThe page references an \"evaluate_forward_fn()\" function and mentions modifying it for new domains, but doesn't detail what specific metric scores discovered agents. The evaluation mechanism isn't explicitly described in this repository excerpt.\n\n**Note:** Complete technical details appear to require consulting the full paper (arXiv:2408.08435) or website linked in the repository.","durationMs":5518,"url":"https://github.com/ShengranHu/ADAS"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"b4435a8b-dd25-457e-95f2-23f77fb9871f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
{"parentUuid":"987b3674-196e-46a6-8dfe-af8f7494e0f7","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"dcbe4efb-6e32-4db6-a75a-aa49b911d737","agentId":"a618fae97ae923ec1","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RrJsUYD5uL31q4vnYJW6v9","type":"tool_result","content":"# Voyager: Key Claims Extract\n\n**1. GPT-4 Blackbox Queries (No Fine-tuning)**\n\"Voyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning.\"\n\n**2. Three Core Components**\n\"Voyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism...\"\n\n**3. Skills Added Without Core Modification**\n\"The skills developed by Voyager are temporally extended, interpretable, and compositional, which compounds the agent's abilities rapidly and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\"\n\n**4. Self-Verification Loop**\n\"By providing the agent's current state and the task to GPT-4, we ask it to act as a critic and inform us whether the program achieves the task.\"\n\n**5. Headline Performance Metrics**\n\"It obtains 3.3x more unique items, travels 2.3x longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3x faster than prior SOTA.\""}]},"uuid":"ee0b2a77-2b11-4121-b48f-bc3434d22ca9","timestamp":"2026-06-21T07:35:24.632Z","toolUseResult":{"bytes":46665,"code":200,"codeText":"OK","result":"# Voyager: Key Claims Extract\n\n**1. GPT-4 Blackbox Queries (No Fine-tuning)**\n\"Voyager interacts with GPT-4 via blackbox queries, which bypasses the need for model parameter fine-tuning.\"\n\n**2. Three Core Components**\n\"Voyager consists of three key components: 1) an automatic curriculum that maximizes exploration, 2) an ever-growing skill library of executable code for storing and retrieving complex behaviors, and 3) a new iterative prompting mechanism...\"\n\n**3. Skills Added Without Core Modification**\n\"The skills developed by Voyager are temporally extended, interpretable, and compositional, which compounds the agent's abilities rapidly and alleviates catastrophic forgetting.\"\n\n**4. Self-Verification Loop**\n\"By providing the agent's current state and the task to GPT-4, we ask it to act as a critic and inform us whether the program achieves the task.\"\n\n**5. Headline Performance Metrics**\n\"It obtains 3.3x more unique items, travels 2.3x longer distances, and unlocks key tech tree milestones up to 15.3x faster than prior SOTA.\"","durationMs":4340,"url":"https://voyager.minedojo.org/"},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"987b3674-196e-46a6-8dfe-af8f7494e0f7","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/gg/Work/Yogi","sessionId":"d8d6b712-ec33-4776-a194-d9a72216a25f","version":"2.1.183","gitBranch":"main","slug":"bright-wondering-lantern"}
